"{\"uid\": \"www.truth-out.org.-opinion-item-36696-we-don-t-need-trump-or-brexit-to-reject-the-credo-of-neoliberal-market-inevitabi-Part3\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"capitalism even 50 years ago that is not only theological but apocalyptic in its refusal to acknowledge limits.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 111, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It has produced a global, social and economic order that is increasingly feudal, while also connected via digital technologies.\", \"from\": 112, \"to\": 239, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Economic historian Karl Polanyi warned in 1944 that a false utopian belief in the ability of unfettered markets to produce naturally balanced outcomes would produce instead a dystopian \\\"stark utopia.\\\"\", \"from\": 241, \"to\": 441, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Today's political chaos represents a spontaneous and uncoordinated eruption of resistance against this encroaching sense of inevitable dystopianism.\", \"from\": 442, \"to\": 590, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As Barber noted, what he refers to as \\\"Jihad\\\" is not a strictly Islamic phenomenon.\", \"from\": 591, \"to\": 674, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is localism, tribalism, particularism or sometimes classical republicanism taking a stand, often violently, acting as de facto social and political antibodies against the viral contagions of McWorld.\", \"from\": 675, \"to\": 877, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pessimistic Optimism  The historically ordained march of theologized neoliberal capitalism depends for its continuation on a belief by individuals that they are powerless against putatively inevitable forces of market-driven globalization.\", \"from\": 879, \"to\": 1118, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is too early to know where the widely divergent outbreaks of resistance on display in 2016 will lead, not least because they are uncoordinated, often self-contradictory or profoundly undemocratic, and are arising in a maelstrom of confusion about core causation.\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1384, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One lesson nonetheless seems clear.\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1421, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The \\\"power of the powerless\\\" has been awakened globally.\", \"from\": 1422, \"to\": 1478, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Whether this awakening will spark a movement towards equitable, ecologically sustainable democratic self-governance is an open question.\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1615, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many of today's leading political theorists caution against an outdated Enlightenment belief in progress and extol the virtues of philosophic pessimism as a hedge against historically groundless optimism.\", \"from\": 1616, \"to\": 1820, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Amid today's fevered populist excitements triggered by a failure of utopian faith in market inevitability, such cautionary thinking seems like sound political advice.\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1987, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright, Truthout.\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 2009, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"May not be reprinted without permission.\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2050, \"entities\": []}]}"